results.name: Least prime that ends a complete Cunningham chain (of the first kind) of length n.
comment: "Complete" means that this chain is not part of a longer Cunningham chain of the first kind.
link: Chris Caldwell's Prime Glossary, Cunn ingham chains.
example: 41->83->167 is a Cunningham chain of the first kind. It is complete because neither (41-1)/2 nor 2*167+1 is prime. It is the first such chain of three primes, so a(3) = 167.
xref: Cf. A110059 for Cunningham chains of the second kind.
